      • hasJsonKey

        public boolean hasJsonKey()
        Description copied from interface: IModelDefinition
        Indicates if a flag's value can be used as a property name in the containing object in JSON who's value will be the object containing the flag. In such cases, the flag will not appear in the object. This is only allowed if the flag is required, as determined by a true result from IFlagInstance.isRequired(). The IFlagInstance can be retrieved using IModelDefinition.getJsonKeyFlagInstance().
        Specified by:
        hasJsonKey in interface IModelDefinition
        Returns:
